<p>How can I do a JOIN inside a Model Table with TableGateway?</p>  <p>I have this in my Model/NoticiasTable.php:</p>  <pre><code>  protected $tableGateway;    public function __construct(TableGateway $tableGateway) {     $this-&gt;tableGateway = $tableGateway;   }    public function fetchAll() {     $where = new Where();     $where-&gt;isNull('deleted_at');      $resultSet = $this-&gt;tableGateway-&gt;select(function (Select $select) use ($where) {       $select-&gt;join('news_photos', 'news_photos.news_id = news.id');       $select-&gt;where($where);       $select-&gt;order('date DESC');     });     return $resultSet;   } </code></pre>  <p>It doesn't show any errors, but the result is empty... If I remove the "join" it works. So, how to use JOIN inside a Model Table?</p>